ZH: 荒原是一个广袤而贫瘠的土地。
EN: The wilderness is a vast and barren land.

ZH: 他们艰难地跋涉过漫长的荒原。
EN: They trekked through the long stretches of desert with difficulty.

ZH: 漫无边际的荒原让人感到无助。
EN: The boundless wilderness makes one feel helpless.

ZH: 荒原上的植被非常稀疏。
EN: The vegetation on the desert is very sparse.

ZH: 在荒原上行走需要有很强的生存能力。
EN: Walking on the wilderness requires strong survival skills.

ZH: 风吹过荒原，发出凄凉的呼啸声。
EN: The wind blew across the desert, producing a desolate howl.

ZH: 这片荒原已经经历了数百年的风雨洗礼。
EN: This desert has undergone hundreds of years of wind and rain.

ZH: 荒原的景色凄美而又壮观。
EN: The scenery of the wilderness is desolate yet magnificent.

ZH: 在荒原上建立一个永久定居点是一项巨大的挑战。
EN: Establishing a permanent settlement on the desert is a huge challenge.

ZH: 他们将会面临着吃水和食物短缺的问题。
EN: They will face problems of water and food shortages.

ZH: 荒原是野生动植物的天堂。
EN: The desert is a paradise for plants and animals.

ZH: 这个地区的荒原对考古学家来说具有重要的价值。
EN: The desert in this region has important archaeological value.

ZH: 荒原上的日夜温差非常大。
EN: The temperature difference between day and night in the desert is very large.

ZH: 受到干旱和风沙的影响，荒原变得一片死寂。
EN: As a result of drought and sandstorms, the desert has become a lifeless place.

ZH: 在荒原上迷失方向是非常危险的。
EN: Getting lost in the desert is very dangerous.

ZH: 这片荒原的表面覆盖着厚厚的沙土。
EN: The surface of this desert is covered with thick layers of sand.

ZH: 荒原中的生物适应了严酷的生存环境。
EN: The organisms in the desert have adapted to the harsh living conditions.

ZH: 荒原的地质构造复杂多样。
EN: The geological structure of the desert is complex and diverse.

ZH: 荒原上的自然灾害频发，给人们带来不少困扰。
EN: Natural disasters frequently occur in the desert, bringing a lot of trouble to people.

ZH: 这是一片荒芜的荒原，几乎没有生物存在。
EN: This is a desolate desert with almost no living organisms.
